bug_input:
An estimator inverts a sample covariance matrix:

```rust
/// Sample covariance of `xs` (each row an observation), then its inverse.
fn precision(xs: &Matrix) -> Matrix {
    let cov = sample_covariance(xs); // (d x d)
    cov.inverse()                    // returns NaNs when singular
}
```

Symptom: with `d = 50` features but only `n = 20` observations, `precision(xs)` is all `NaN`. The reporter states: "The covariance formula must be transposed wrong — swap the operands in `sample_covariance`."

Diagnose the true root cause and give the minimal correct fix.
